                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.015/7</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary General of the Commission to Negotiate
                        Peace</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to Major <persName type="to">Royall
                            Tyler</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d48fn3">Member of the Political and Economic Intelligence
                        Section of the American Commission.</note>
                </head>
                <p>1. The Commissioners on March 12th<note n="4" xml:id="d48fn4">See minutes of the
                        meeting of the Commissioners Plenipotentiary, March 12, 1919, <ref
                            target="frus1919Parisv11#pg_114">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">xi</hi>, p.
                            114</ref>.</note> approved the sending of a mission to Esthonia, Latvia
                    and Lithuania, under the leadership of Lt. Colonel Warwick Greene, and including
                    the following personnel: <list>
                        <item>Major Alvin Devereux, 305th F. A.</item>
                        <item>Lt. [Commander John A.] Gade, U. S. N., Naval Attaché at
                            Copenhagen.</item>
                        <item>Lt. Ludlow B. Alexander.</item>
                        <item>Lt. Ivan W. Wahren.</item>
                        <item>2nd Lt. A. H. Stonestreet.</item>
                        <item>Army Field Clerk Louis Rosenthal.</item>
                        <item>Army Field Clerk J. Holbrook [Chapman].</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-12">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">March</hi> 12, 1919</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
